fields.description:
In the MetaStoreDirectSql class when IN clause is used, the query statement is created via string concatenation.

Since JDBC API allows only one literal for one “?” parameter, PreparedStatement doesn’t work for IN clause queries. To create the PreparedStatement query dynamically based on the size of the elements in IN clause, the makeParams() should be used instead of concatenation.
fields.summary: Create PreparedStatement query dynamically when IN clause is used
